    "summary": "In 2002 I joined TNT (Post NL) as controller within the postal environment, then moved to a role of senior controller of a sorting centre and then was promoted to Manager Business Control & Facilities. I supported several change processes and reorganizations and also contributed to various Headoffice projects.\nIn 2007 I moved to TNT Express as Manager Administration for TNT Netherlands. In that role, I was responsible for the Invoice to Cash process including the processes of billing and customer administration, collection and dispute & claim. In these teams worked 50+ professionals. A new SAP system FSCM was introduced to support the collection, risk and dispute processes. Next to the focus on working capital, we focused on improving customer experience from a finance perspective.\nNext to this role I started early 2013 as project manager to outsource transactional activities to a Shared Service Centre.\nEnd of 2014 I was promoted to Manager Business Control, responsible for the planning and control process for TNT Netherlands, Belgium and Luxembourg. \nEarly 2017 I joined the Benelux integration team responsible for all finance activities in the Benelux for both FedEx and TNT. \nMid 2017 I joined the Benelux PSP board, covering finance for the combination of FedEx and TNT in the Benelux. \nI moved after the summer in 2019 to a position of Manager FP&A International, in which I will create a new International team that will support Special Services globally and support the Finance Transformation.  \nMarch 2023 I joined the Europe payroll team as Senior Manager Payroll Europe. In this role I will be responsible for the payroll process for all FedEx employees in Europe. Leading a team of 100+ professionals supporting 32 countries. \n\nSpecialties: General Management, Business Control, Working Capital Management, Coaching, Performance Management, Change Programs and Project Management.\n\nCompetences: result driven, people manager, change management, analytical skills, customer focus, communication skills and teamwork.",
